messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 3/23/2005 7:11:57 AM Central Standard Time,
UnschoolingDiscussion@yahoogroups.com writes:

I bought her cookie cutters and receipe books from e bay and printed them
off the internet and she has turned her cookie love into a little hobby and
sells the cookies to her friends, on a stall each year and gives them wrapped as
gifts.



On a side note, our family visited the cookie cutter museum in Joplin,
Missouri yesterday. There are cookie cutter clubs and exchanges throughout the
world. Amazing how the littlist items can turn out so BIG.

Spc in Mo
